==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} as if *{{term||inflammabilis|lang=la}}, from {{term|inflammare||to set on fire}}, from {{term|in||in, on}} + {{term|flamma||flame}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|ĭnʹflăm-ə-bəl}}, {{IPA|/ɪnˈflæməbəl/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/In"fl{m@b@l/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Capable of burning; easily set on [[fire]].
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} Easily excited; [[set off]] by the slightest excuse; easily [[enrage]]d or [[inflame]]d.

====Usage notes====
* {{term||Inflammable}} can be misinterpreted as an [[antonym]] of {{term|flammable}} and so taken to have the opposite meaning to that intended. Where such confusion might arise, especially where this may be a safety hazard, one may prefer to use {{term|flammable}} or another [[synonym]].

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|capable of burning}} [[combustible]], [[flammable]]
* {{sense|easily excited}} [[hot-headed]], [[quick]] to [[anger]]

====Antonyms====
* {{sense|capable of burning}} [[fireproof]], [[incombustible]], [[non-flammable]]
* {{sense|easily excited}} [[level-headed]], [[unflappable]]

====Related terms====
* [[inflammability]]
* [[inflammation]]
* [[inflame]]

